  "critical": false,
  "description": "Visual and acoustic signaling systems for long-distance communication before electrical technology: signal fires, beacons, semaphore lines (Chappe telegraph), heliograph (mirror signaling), and flag signaling. Ranges from 5 km (signal fires) to 100+ km (heliograph). The first telecommunications infrastructure, enabling military coordination and emergency warning across distances impractical for couriers.",
